{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"claimEarned pays fixed rewards immediately and can be repeated indefinitely for the same stake","locations":["0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:999","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:1007","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:1023"],"claim":"claimEarned iterates over every stake and adds amount * apr / 10000 without checking whether endstakeAt has passed and without marking any reward as settled. The function only updates stakeAt, but stakeAt is never used by earnedToken, unstake, or claimEarned to determine eligibility, so the same stake can generate the same payout on every call, including before lock expiry.","impact":"Any staker can drain the pooled staking token balance by repeatedly calling claimEarned, extracting rewards that were never earned and exhausting funds needed to repay other users' principal and rewards.","paths":["Create any stake in any plan and call claimEarned immediately, before the plan's lock duration ends.","Call claimEarned again in later transactions; each call recomputes the same fixed reward from the unchanged stake amount and transfers it again."] ,"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Rewards claimed via claimEarned are paid again during unstake","locations":["0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:948","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:964","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:999","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:1023"],"claim":"claimEarned does not reduce stake principal or record that a stake's reward has already been consumed for later withdrawals. unstake separately recomputes rewards from the amount being withdrawn once endstakeAt has passed, so a user who has already claimed can still receive the same reward again when unstaking the same matured principal.","impact":"Even if repeated claimEarned abuse were somehow constrained, matured positions can still be double-paid through the normal claim-then-unstake flow, accelerating insolvency of the staking pool.","paths":["Wait until a stake matures, call claimEarned once, then call unstake for the same amount.","claimEarned transfers the APR reward first; unstake later recomputes amount * apr / 10000 for the withdrawn matured amount and transfers that reward again."] ,"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Owner can arbitrarily sweep staked tokens and leave the pool insolvent","locations":["0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:893","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:910","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:1076"],"claim":"User deposits are held directly in the contract's stakingToken balance, and penaltyWithdraw lets the owner transfer out any amount strictly below that balance without reserving assets for outstanding principal, matured withdrawals, or promised rewards. No accounting fence prevents owner withdrawals from consuming user funds.","impact":"The owner can rug most of the staking pool, causing user unstakes and reward claims to fail or become undercollateralized.","paths":["Users stake tokens, which accumulate in the contract balance.","The owner calls penaltyWithdraw with nearly the full token balance.","Subsequent unstake or claimEarned calls no longer have enough tokens backing them."] ,"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Core staking flows ignore ERC20 return values and can mutate accounting after failed token transfers","locations":["0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:893","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:979","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:985","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:986","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:1029","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:1030","0xa1ce40702e15d0417a6c74d0bab96772f36f4e99/contracts/WIFStaking.sol:1063"],"claim":"Although the contract imports SafeERC20, stake, unstake, claimEarned, and emergencyWithdraw use raw transfer/transferFrom calls and do not check their boolean return values. For tokens that return false instead of reverting, these functions can proceed after a failed token movement and still record stake creation, reduce user stake amounts, or account rewards as if payment succeeded.","impact":"With a false-returning or otherwise non-compliant staking token, users can lose principal or reward entitlement in contract state without actually receiving tokens, and the protocol can record stake positions that were never funded.","paths":["If transferFrom returns false in stake, the function can still append a new stake entry using the observed balance delta, potentially creating a zero-funded or underfunded position.","If transfer returns false in unstake, claimEarned, or emergencyWithdraw, the function can complete after decrementing stake amounts or incrementing reward totals even though no tokens were delivered."] ,"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Double counting bug in claimEarned totalRewards calculation","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Confirmed, but totalRewards and related counters are not used to gate payouts or permissions anywhere in the contract; this is bookkeeping corruption only, not realistic protocol-level harm on its own."},{"title":"claimEarned missing nonReentrant modifier","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Speculative and not needed to exploit the contract. The reportable issue is the missing reward-settlement logic itself; adding nonReentrant would not prevent the observed drain."},{"title":"Stake amount can be reduced to zero without updating stakesCount","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Inaccurate or stale counting can waste gas and misreport pool metadata, but it does not create realistic fund loss, lockup, or protocol insolvency."},{"title":"earnedToken rewards are not time-proportional","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The contract implements fixed-plan rewards paid on maturity, not linear vesting. Using apr as a label is misleading, but the code is internally consistent with fixed-per-plan payouts."},{"title":"Owner can permanently disable staking plans with no recovery","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is an owner-controlled configuration choice for new deposits, not an exploitable vulnerability affecting existing funds."},{"title":"emergencyWithdraw allows withdrawal during lock period","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The function name and logic indicate an intentional early-exit path. It does deduct 20% from the withdrawn amount, so the claim that users exit with no penalty is unsupported."},{"title":"No event emitted for critical state changes","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Transparency issue only; not a reportable protocol-level vulnerability."},{"title":"Uninitialized staking struct pushed to array","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Solidity initializes the new struct to zero values before explicit field assignment. No exploitable behavior follows from this pattern here."},{"title":"Missing input validation for _stakingId in claimEarned","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"plans is a mapping, so out-of-range ids do not create unsafe memory access; invalid ids simply reference empty/default storage and do not create material harm."},{"title":"Unused penalty state variable","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"penalty is used in emergencyWithdraw. The commented burn transfer is better understood as part of the broader owner-custody issue already captured by penaltyWithdraw, not a separate standalone bug."}]}
